Heat oven to 350 degrees F. Spray two 10-ounce custard cups with cooking spray. Toss pears, cranberries, sugar, flour and cinnamon in medium bowl and spoon into custard cups. Toss granola and butter in small bowl; sprinkle over fruit. Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until hot and bubbly. Enjoy topped with ice cream, if you like.